-- MOVES- JP Morgan Chase, Standard Chartered, BlackRock
-- 
-- Mon Mar 24, 2014 06:40AM EDT
-- None



March 24 (Reuters) - The following financial services industry appointments were announced on Monday. To inform us of other job changes, email moves@thomsonreuters.com.

** JP MORGAN CHASE & CO <JPM.N> JP Morgan Chase & Co's chief executive for China investment banking, Fang Fang, will leave the firm, according to an internal memo - a departure that comes amid a probe of JP Morgan hiring practices in Asia. The memo gave no reason for his resignation. [ID:nL1N0ML038]  ** STANDARD CHARTERED BANK PLC <STAN.L> The Asia-focused lender named Neeraj Swaroop as chief executive of its bank in Singapore, effective March 31. Swaroop most recently served as CEO for ASEAN, excluding Singapore.  ** BLACKROCK INC <BLK.N>